<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/998> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #998" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commanded the left wing under Papirius at Aquilonia (Liv. 10.40.7, and 41.9-14)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/986> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #986" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/981> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #981" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pro praetore in Fabius' absence from camp (Liv. 10.25.11, and 26.12). Was defeated there (10.26.8-12), but served, perhaps as Legate, under Fabius at Sentinum (10.29.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/968> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #968" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Rullianus in Samnium (Liv. 10.14.14)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/959> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #959" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.11.10; Act. Tr. (on Fulvius); Chr. 354 (Scipione et Centumalo) Fast. Hyd. (Scipione et Maximo), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 38f., 111, 424f. According to Livy, Scipio won a victory in Etruria (10.12.3-8), but according to the Elogium (CIL 1\n     , 2.7; ILS 1) he captured Taurasia and Cisauna of Samnium and subdued Lucania.\n     \n      1\n     \n     According to Act. Tr., Fulvius was victorious in Etruria and Samnium but Livy (10.12.3 and 9, and 13.1) records only that he took Bovianum and Aufidena of Samnium, and celebrated a triumph (Degrassi 72f., 543). Frontinus (Str. 1.6.1-2, and 11.2) takes him to Lucania." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/943> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #943" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 1\n     .2.7 (ILS 1). Seidel (14) places him in 301, an odd numbered year before his consulate. As the Aediles of 299 are known, 301 is the latest possible date." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7228> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7228" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 298. See MRR 1.174. According to A. La Regina the Lucanians he subdued were a northern group who inhabited the Sangro valley and were later forgotten (Dial. di ArcheoL 2, 1968, 173-190). On Barbatus (ILLRP 309) and the other inscriptions from the Tomb of the Scipios with the names of Scipios who were magistrates, and members of their families, see ILLRP nos. 310-317. See also A. La Regina, above; F. Zevi, Stud. Misc. 15, 1969-70, 69ff.; F. Coarelli, Dial. di Archeol. 6, 1972, 36-106.[71]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1062> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1062" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elog., CIL 1\n     .2.7; ILS 1; Fest. 237 M- 270 L (as restored by De Boor, Fast. Cens. 77f.: <...Domitius Corne>liusque <censores fecerunt P. Valerio Ti.> Corun<canio cos...>)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1061> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1061" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The Elogium gives no clue to the date of Scipio's censorship, and Festus as restored is insecure evidence. Scipio could have been the unknown patrician colleague of Caedicius in 283. If so, Fabius Gurges (suggested here in CIL) could have been Censor in either 289 or 280. See 289, Censors; Degrassi, 113." .
